			title: "What's That Block?"
			icon: "minecraft:glass"
			description: [
				"§6Jade§f adds a small floating tooltip at the top of your screen showing"
				"§freal-time information about whatever you are looking at."
				""
				"§eWhat Jade shows by default:§r"
				"§7• Block or entity name and which mod added it."
				"§7• §6Create§7 machines: current speed (RPM), stress load, and what they are doing."
				"§7• §6Ars Nouveau§7 Source Jars: current Source level and capacity."
				"§7• §6Alex's Mobs§7 creatures: health, hunger, tame status, and mood."
				"§7• §6MineColonies§7 citizens: name, profession, and current task."
				"§7• §6Sophisticated Storage§7: contents preview for chests."
				"§7• §6Farmer's Delight§7 Cooking Pot: what is currently cooking and progress."
				""
				"§eCustomising Jade:§r"
				"§7• While in-game: hold §eU§7 then press §eC§7 to open the Jade config screen."
				"§7• Toggle individual information modules on or off."
				"§7• Reduce clutter: disable modules you never use (e.g. block hardness info)."
				"§7• Change the tooltip §eposition§7 to any screen corner via the config."
				""
				"§7Jade is installed on both client and server — information is accurate"
				"§7for both singleplayer and multiplayer sessions."
				""
				"§a► Task: Look at any block. When the name tooltip appears at the top of"
				"§ayour screen, mark this quest complete."
			]
			dependencies: ["000A0001"]
		}
