			title: "Read the Fine Print"
			icon: "minecraft:enchanted_book"
			description: [
				"§6Enchantment Descriptions§f adds plain-English tooltips to every enchanted"
				"§fbook and enchanted item so you know exactly what each enchantment does."
				""
				"§eWithout this mod:§r §7Hover a book — you see '§eSharpness III§7'."
				"§eWith this mod:§r §7'§eSharpness III§7 — Increases melee attack damage."
				"§7  Adds 1.5 extra damage per level (4.5 extra at Sharpness III)."
				"§7  Can be applied to swords and axes.'"
				""
				"§eWhy it matters for this pack:§r"
				"§7• §6Ars Nouveau§7 adds unique enchantments for spell amplification and"
				"§7  Source regen. Without descriptions, new players have no idea what they do."
				"§7• §6Create: New Age§7 adds electrical efficiency enchantments for motors."
				"§7• §6Alex's Mobs§7 adds weapon enchantments for rare creature drops."
				"§7• §6Enigmatic Legacy§7 charms (Ch 3.3) have passive perk text."
				"§7• §6Tetra§7 modular components also carry enchantable properties."
				""
				"§eHow to get an enchanted book for this task:§r"
				"§7• Loot §6any chest§7 in a YUNG's dungeon, village library, or bastion."
				"§7• Trade with a §6Librarian villager§7 (best source for specific enchants)."
				"§7• Build an §6Enchanting Table§7 and enchant a plain book with XP."
				"§7• The §6Lootr§7 mod gives every family member their own loot roll in"
				"§7  dungeon chests — enchanted books are very common drops."
				""
				"§7Note: Enchantment Descriptions is §eclient-side only§7. It is not installed"
				"§7on the server — it only works while you are playing on your own machine."
				""
				"§a► Task: Have any enchanted book in your inventory. It is not consumed."
			]
			dependencies: ["000A0002"]
		}
