			title: "See What You Eat"
			icon: "minecraft:apple"
			description: [
				"§6AppleSkin§f makes the hidden hunger saturation system visible on every"
				"§ffood item tooltip — so you finally know why cooked meals matter."
				""
				"§eThe hunger system explained:§r"
				"§7• The §eFood Bar§7 (drumsticks, bottom of screen) is what you can see."
				"§7• §eSaturation§7 is an invisible second meter that depletes first."
				"§7• When saturation is full, the food bar never drains."
				"§7• When saturation hits zero, the food bar starts draining normally."
				"§7• §fHigh-saturation food§7 = you stay full much longer between meals."
				""
				"§eAppleSkin additions:§r"
				"§7• §eGreen bar§7 on food tooltips = saturation value (longer = better)."
				"§7• Hover food while hungry = §epredicted§7 food bar state shown on tooltip."
				"§7• Small §esaturation shimmer§7 on the HUD when saturation is high."
				""
				"§ePractical comparison in this pack:§r"
				"§7• §fBread§7: 2.5 hunger + 6.0 saturation."
				"§7• §fCooked Chicken§7: 3.0 hunger + 7.2 saturation."
				"§7• §6Farmer's Delight Stew§7: 3.0 hunger + §e12.0 saturation§7."
				"§7  A Farmer's Delight meal keeps you full §e2× longer§7 at the same"
				"§7  hunger cost. This is why the Cooking Pot is worth building early."
				""
				"§7AppleSkin is §eclient-side only§7 — not installed on the server."
				""
				"§a► Task: Hover any food item in your inventory or JEI panel."
				"§aWhen the tooltip shows the green saturation bar, mark complete."
			]
			dependencies: ["000A0001"]
		}
