				""
				"§eCrafting:§r"
				"§7• 4× §eArcanite Dust§7 (around the edges) + 1× §eCompass§7 (centre)."
				"§7• §eArcanite Dust§7 comes from §6Ars Nouveau§7 — craft it from §eSource Gems§7"
				"§7  at a crafting table (Source Gems → grind into dust)."
				"§7• Source Gems drop from §6magical creatures§7 or grow from §6Source Berry§7 plants."
				"§7• If you have not started Ch 1 yet: explore near the spawn area and"
				"§7  look for §6Archwood Trees§7 or a §6Starbuncle§7 creature to find early gems."
				""
				"§eUsing the Compass:§r"
				"§7• Right-click → biome search GUI opens."
				"§7• Type any biome name — autocomplete shows all matches including Terralith."
				"§7• Select a biome → the compass needle points toward the nearest instance."
				"§7• Walk in that direction — the needle updates live."
				"§7• Biomes can be 500–5,000 blocks away in a large Terralith world."
				"§7  Take a §6Steam 'n' Rails§7 train when one is built — saves time."
				""
				"§eBiomes worth hunting:§r"
				"§7• §6Moonlit Grove§7 — Archwood Trees spawn most densely here (Ch 1 magic)."
				"§7• §6Skylands§7 or §6Skylands Autumn§7 — floating islands, dramatic build spots."
				"§7• §6Volcanic Peaks§7 — unique underground resources in Alex's Caves below."
				"§7• §6Glacial Chasm§7 — connects thematically to Twilight Forest Snow Queen."
				"§7• §6Scarlet Mountains§7 — stunning red landscape for base aesthetics."
				""
				"§a► Task: Craft a Nature's Compass and have it in your inventory."
